WEBVTT

00:00:01.263 --> 00:00:03.397
[Hickman stunned]
<i>This was your beat?</i>

00:00:04.378 --> 00:00:06.145
Yeah. Italian border,

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:08.214
from here all the way
up to Switzerland.

00:00:08.249 --> 00:00:09.582
It's a hell of
a lot more picturesque

00:00:09.633 --> 00:00:11.000
than where I worked.

00:00:11.034 --> 00:00:13.870
Well, the longer
you police an area,

00:00:13.904 --> 00:00:14.904
the harder it is

00:00:14.939 --> 00:00:16.105
to appreciate picturesque.

00:00:16.140 --> 00:00:18.925
Lot of human-trafficking
through here?

00:00:18.976 --> 00:00:20.026
More all the time.

00:00:20.060 --> 00:00:21.377
I was working on
a joint operation,

00:00:21.412 --> 00:00:23.246
with some of
the other border regions.

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:24.914
I'd like to see
that investigation

00:00:24.949 --> 00:00:27.433
if you still have access.

00:00:27.468 --> 00:00:29.519
That's why
you asked me to bring you

00:00:29.553 --> 00:00:31.137
to my old stomping grounds?

00:00:31.188 --> 00:00:32.855
It's related
to Phillip Genovese,

00:00:32.890 --> 00:00:34.974
the files you had me gather?

00:00:35.009 --> 00:00:37.093
It may have something
to do with Genovese.

00:00:37.111 --> 00:00:38.394
I don't know.

00:00:38.428 --> 00:00:39.479
But I really do want to
familiarize myself

00:00:39.530 --> 00:00:41.047
with the area.

00:00:41.081 --> 00:00:44.000
I guess I could
introduce you to Captain Geroux,

00:00:44.034 --> 00:00:46.435
my former superior.

00:00:46.453 --> 00:00:49.271
And I wouldn't mind checking up
on the progress myself.

00:00:49.290 --> 00:00:51.273
Great.

00:00:52.409 --> 00:00:53.993
You mean now, don't you?

00:00:56.130 --> 00:00:58.214
[♪]

00:01:04.054 --> 00:01:06.973
[Moans echoing]

00:01:12.462 --> 00:01:16.182
[Echoing laughter]

00:01:19.703 --> 00:01:21.404
[♪]

00:01:21.438 --> 00:01:24.941
You said you'd take me
dancing before the party.

00:01:24.975 --> 00:01:26.359
Yeah...

00:01:26.410 --> 00:01:28.344
But we need to send
the bodyguards first.

00:01:28.379 --> 00:01:31.310
Then send them.
You promised me!

00:01:32.983 --> 00:01:34.434
Okay, okay.

00:01:34.468 --> 00:01:35.418
[She giggles]

00:01:38.539 --> 00:01:40.373
[Speaking French]

00:01:40.424 --> 00:01:42.041
[Phone rings]

00:01:44.428 --> 00:01:46.996
[Ringing]

00:01:47.014 --> 00:01:48.047
This is Jacques.

00:01:48.098 --> 00:01:50.016
Jacques, we're going to a club.

00:01:50.050 --> 00:01:51.017
The, um...?

00:01:51.051 --> 00:01:52.051
Mecca.

00:01:52.102 --> 00:01:53.436
The Mecca. In town.

00:01:53.470 --> 00:01:55.471
Girl: <i>Don't forget</i>
<i>the party after!</i>

00:01:55.505 --> 00:01:58.674
I gave them the address
when I got here.

00:01:58.692 --> 00:02:00.509
And then a private party.

00:02:00.527 --> 00:02:02.228
<i>You have the address.</i>

00:02:02.279 --> 00:02:04.013
I'll send the advance team now.

00:02:04.031 --> 00:02:05.231
[Men respond in affirmative]

00:02:05.282 --> 00:02:07.016
Give us half an hour.

00:02:07.034 --> 00:02:08.401
[♪]

00:02:08.452 --> 00:02:09.569
Half an hour.

00:02:12.322 --> 00:02:15.375
Whatever will we do?

00:02:17.378 --> 00:02:19.528
[Horn honks]

00:02:19.546 --> 00:02:21.514
[Club music pounding]

00:02:23.700 --> 00:02:25.251
- Ca va?
- Ca va.

00:02:25.302 --> 00:02:27.136
[Music thumping]

00:02:28.505 --> 00:02:30.390
[♪]

00:02:42.519 --> 00:02:44.687
[Radio crackles]
Inspected first location now.

00:02:44.722 --> 00:02:48.608
It's dark, crowded
and impossible to control.

00:02:48.659 --> 00:02:49.659
Maxim's going to love it here.

00:02:49.693 --> 00:02:52.495
No comments, just do the job.

00:02:52.529 --> 00:02:53.579
[Crackles]

00:02:53.614 --> 00:02:55.231
[♪]

00:03:11.548 --> 00:03:13.266
[Electric lock beeps]

00:03:15.252 --> 00:03:17.053
Okay.

00:03:17.087 --> 00:03:20.440
Get him straight
to the V.I.P. area.

00:03:20.474 --> 00:03:22.442
It's a much safer environment.

00:03:22.476 --> 00:03:24.610
Check out the second venue.

00:03:24.645 --> 00:03:26.239
I'll get the package rolling.

00:03:27.264 --> 00:03:28.264
[Music filtering out]

00:03:35.739 --> 00:03:38.207
Head to
the private party venue.

00:03:41.411 --> 00:03:44.163
[Truck rumbling past]

00:04:07.237 --> 00:04:08.804
[♪]

00:04:08.822 --> 00:04:09.856
We can go to the club now.

00:04:11.708 --> 00:04:13.359
Party time.

00:04:13.410 --> 00:04:15.278
[Clink]

00:04:19.166 --> 00:04:21.150
There's no one here.

00:04:22.819 --> 00:04:25.671
This is the address
she gave me.

00:04:25.706 --> 00:04:29.425
Okay, so where is the party?

00:04:32.396 --> 00:04:34.297
Jacques?

00:04:34.331 --> 00:04:36.682
I might have a bad address
on the party.

00:04:36.717 --> 00:04:39.101
[Radio crackling] Advance one?

00:04:39.136 --> 00:04:42.638
Advance one?
Can you hear me?

00:04:42.672 --> 00:04:44.690
Come in, advance one.

00:04:44.725 --> 00:04:46.692
Hello?

00:04:46.727 --> 00:04:49.812
[Radio crackles, then silence]

00:04:49.846 --> 00:04:51.614
[Radio crackling]

00:04:51.648 --> 00:04:53.515
Something's wrong?

00:04:53.534 --> 00:04:55.318
I lost their signal.

00:04:55.352 --> 00:04:56.369
Maybe they're having

00:04:56.403 --> 00:04:59.355
a little bit of fun for once.

00:04:59.373 --> 00:05:00.573
[Laughing]

00:05:00.624 --> 00:05:02.441
[Car engine revs]

00:05:11.168 --> 00:05:14.136
Go around the block
until the "Z" -list gets inside.

00:05:14.171 --> 00:05:15.704
Stuck, boss.

00:05:15.722 --> 00:05:16.839
[Horn blares]

00:05:16.873 --> 00:05:19.258
Leave the car here.
Let's get inside.

00:05:19.309 --> 00:05:20.593
[♪]

00:05:23.764 --> 00:05:27.650
[Crowd buzzing]

00:05:27.684 --> 00:05:29.151
[Cameras click]

00:05:29.186 --> 00:05:31.187
[People cheer]

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:37.743
[Club music thumping]

00:05:37.778 --> 00:05:38.894
Maxim: Where's Laure?

00:05:38.912 --> 00:05:40.413
She's behind us!

00:05:40.447 --> 00:05:42.564
Let's get upstairs.

00:05:42.583 --> 00:05:45.668
[♪]

00:05:50.958 --> 00:05:53.793
[♪]

00:05:55.512 --> 00:05:56.796
[Fires shot]

00:05:56.847 --> 00:05:58.247
[Firing]

00:05:58.265 --> 00:06:00.299
[Fires shot]

00:06:00.350 --> 00:06:02.751
[Shots blasting]

00:06:02.769 --> 00:06:05.438
[♪]

00:06:09.426 --> 00:06:10.559
[Fires]

00:06:10.593 --> 00:06:12.612
No!

00:06:12.646 --> 00:06:14.280
[Shot fires]

00:06:15.432 --> 00:06:16.983
[Shot fires]

00:06:18.535 --> 00:06:19.652
[Maxim pants and grunts]

00:06:19.703 --> 00:06:21.487
[♪]

00:06:21.538 --> 00:06:24.490
[Door slams]

00:06:33.250 --> 00:06:37.253
[♪]

00:06:57.182 --> 00:07:00.182
<font color="#ffffff">1x05
Special Ops
Part 1</font>

00:07:00.183 --> 00:07:03.183
==sync, correction by <font color=#00ff00>dcdah</font>==
<font color="#e9be16">Resync for WEB-DL by </font><font color="#ffffff">lost0ne</font>
for www.addic7ed.com

00:07:08.825 --> 00:07:10.419
No ones here.

00:07:10.939 --> 00:07:12.500
Saturday night,

00:07:12.620 --> 00:07:14.101
the joint must be jumpin'.

00:07:14.135 --> 00:07:16.020
Nah. They're at the scene
of a multiple homicide

00:07:16.071 --> 00:07:18.055
and kidnapping in Cannes.

00:07:19.407 --> 00:07:22.192
The joint really is jumpin'.

00:07:23.261 --> 00:07:25.296
Salut, Claude.
Ca va?

00:07:27.949 --> 00:07:30.451
Oui. Combien?

00:07:33.788 --> 00:07:34.922
Oui, peut-etre.

00:07:34.956 --> 00:07:37.424
[Speaks in french]
On n'est pas loin. On arrive.

00:07:38.059 --> 00:07:39.876
This might actually be
a case for us.

00:07:39.911 --> 00:07:41.027
Why do you say that?

00:07:41.062 --> 00:07:43.863
It might match
another kidnapping in Florence

00:07:43.898 --> 00:07:45.165
a few months ago.

00:07:45.199 --> 00:07:46.900
It was in one of the files
Major Daniel had me process.

00:07:46.934 --> 00:07:48.401
You're sure?

00:07:48.435 --> 00:07:49.903
I told you.
I have a memory thing.

00:07:49.937 --> 00:07:52.939
Okay. Let's check it out
with Sebastian.

00:07:55.609 --> 00:07:57.794
[♪]

00:08:05.136 --> 00:08:07.137
<i>[Crowd cheering]</i>

00:08:07.171 --> 00:08:09.455
Dammit!

00:08:09.473 --> 00:08:10.473
[Sighs heavily]

00:08:15.896 --> 00:08:19.182
[Telephone vibrates]

00:08:21.435 --> 00:08:22.435
Anne-Marie?

00:08:22.469 --> 00:08:24.154
Yeah, Sebastian?
Sorry to disturb you

00:08:24.188 --> 00:08:25.805
<i>on a Saturday.</i>

00:08:25.823 --> 00:08:28.692
It's all right.
I'm still at the office.

00:08:28.743 --> 00:08:30.076
I had some work to catch up on.

00:08:30.111 --> 00:08:31.494
Some programming.

00:08:31.529 --> 00:08:33.413
What can I do for you?

00:08:33.447 --> 00:08:35.415
Can you access

00:08:35.449 --> 00:08:37.784
Florentine crime databases
over the last six months?

00:08:37.818 --> 00:08:39.786
Yeah. Hold on.

00:08:47.061 --> 00:08:48.628
What are you looking for?

00:08:48.662 --> 00:08:50.096
There's been a kidnapping
in Cannes.

00:08:50.131 --> 00:08:51.831
It sounds like one in Florence.

00:08:51.849 --> 00:08:53.800
Yes. There're... two,

00:08:53.834 --> 00:08:55.685
one parental abduction,

00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:57.988
<i>one kidnapping for ransom</i>
<i>from a public space</i>

00:08:58.022 --> 00:08:59.806
<i>where the victim's</i>
<i>security team</i>

00:08:59.840 --> 00:09:01.507
was overpowered and...

00:09:01.525 --> 00:09:03.693
Anne-marie: <i>And murdered.</i>
<i>Very similar.</i>

00:09:03.728 --> 00:09:05.729
Yes. Very.

00:09:05.780 --> 00:09:06.846
Uh, no,
I was talking to Hickman.

00:09:06.864 --> 00:09:08.648
You're with Hickman?

00:09:10.017 --> 00:09:11.684
Yeah. Uh, can you call
Major Daniel

00:09:11.702 --> 00:09:13.787
<i>and tell him</i>
<i>we're close to the scene?</i>

00:09:13.821 --> 00:09:15.038
We'll see what we can find out.

00:09:15.072 --> 00:09:16.906
If he doesn't think
the case is for us,

00:09:16.941 --> 00:09:18.191
then we can always pull back.

00:09:18.209 --> 00:09:21.194
- Right.
<i>- Thanks.</i>

00:09:21.212 --> 00:09:23.580
[Click]

00:09:23.631 --> 00:09:25.715
She's with Hickman...

00:09:25.750 --> 00:09:28.034
in Cannes?

00:09:32.173 --> 00:09:36.176
Dinner was lovely.
Thank you.

00:09:37.611 --> 00:09:38.928
I'm going to clean up.

00:09:38.979 --> 00:09:41.731
No, I can do it.

00:09:42.767 --> 00:09:45.235
Um... we can
do it together.

00:10:06.674 --> 00:10:08.208
[Gasps suddenly
and bangs into the chair]

00:10:12.046 --> 00:10:13.880
No.

00:10:13.914 --> 00:10:16.716
It's all right.
It's all right.

00:10:16.750 --> 00:10:19.602
No.

00:10:19.637 --> 00:10:21.221
It's not all right.

00:10:26.060 --> 00:10:27.644
It'll never be all right.

00:10:27.695 --> 00:10:29.762
[♪]

00:10:35.686 --> 00:10:37.287
[Door closes]

00:10:46.280 --> 00:10:48.882
[Cell rings]

00:10:51.252 --> 00:10:53.220
Sebastian.

00:10:53.254 --> 00:10:56.723
No. No, no. I was...

00:10:56.758 --> 00:10:58.141
What can I do for you?

00:10:58.176 --> 00:10:59.343
[Blows landing]

00:10:59.394 --> 00:11:01.294
[♪]

00:11:10.605 --> 00:11:13.073
[Cell ringing]

00:11:13.107 --> 00:11:14.408
Excuse me.

00:11:16.744 --> 00:11:18.695
[Sighs]

00:11:18.746 --> 00:11:21.615
[Panting] Sergeant Vittoria.

00:11:21.649 --> 00:11:22.749
[Boisterous chatter
over background music]

00:11:22.784 --> 00:11:24.785
Cheers, mate.

00:11:30.124 --> 00:11:30.824
There.

00:11:30.842 --> 00:11:32.676
Get that into you.

00:11:32.710 --> 00:11:34.761
[Cell begins ringing]

00:11:37.598 --> 00:11:41.385
Why does the Lord hate me?

00:11:44.306 --> 00:11:45.753
Detective Hickman?

00:11:51.845 --> 00:11:53.012
Captain Claude Geroux.

00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:54.313
Nice to meet you.

00:11:54.348 --> 00:11:56.232
Pleasure to meet you, sir.
I've heard a lot about you.

00:11:56.266 --> 00:11:58.317
Excuse me.

00:12:03.857 --> 00:12:04.973
How was the reunion?

00:12:05.093 --> 00:12:06.623
They're overwhelmed.

00:12:06.743 --> 00:12:09.028
Anybody would be.
Can I see your phone?

00:12:09.062 --> 00:12:11.030
[♪]

00:12:13.534 --> 00:12:14.400
[Shutter snaps]

00:12:16.870 --> 00:12:19.088
Get this photo of that casing
to Sebastian to analyze.

00:12:19.123 --> 00:12:21.290
Mm-hmm.

00:12:21.341 --> 00:12:22.542
They're all
double-tapped.

00:12:24.244 --> 00:12:25.545
One shot centre-mass,
one in the head.

00:12:25.579 --> 00:12:27.280
It's extremely brazen.

00:12:27.314 --> 00:12:29.132
The club was packed.

00:12:29.183 --> 00:12:30.550
They didn't worry about
witnesses describing them.

00:12:30.584 --> 00:12:34.103
Well, if something
is fast and brutal,

00:12:34.138 --> 00:12:35.921
nobody remembers any details.

00:12:35.939 --> 00:12:37.940
It's how the mob works
in New York.

00:12:37.975 --> 00:12:40.610
These kills
were definitely professional.

00:12:40.644 --> 00:12:42.228
[Tires squealing]

00:12:43.530 --> 00:12:44.480
[♪]

00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:04.467
[Tires squealing]

00:13:07.601 --> 00:13:09.519
One more pint and I was
home free

00:13:09.639 --> 00:13:10.851
with the most beautiful
bird I've seen

00:13:10.886 --> 00:13:12.436
since I left Dublin.

00:13:12.470 --> 00:13:13.687
I didn't know
you had a girlfriend.

00:13:13.722 --> 00:13:15.773
There's a lot
you don't know about me.

00:13:15.807 --> 00:13:17.474
Really?

00:13:17.509 --> 00:13:19.526
Where were you
on a Saturday night?

00:13:19.561 --> 00:13:22.763
There's a lot you don't
know about me, either.

00:13:22.797 --> 00:13:24.031
In the gym.

00:13:24.065 --> 00:13:26.116
Dedication.
That's hot.

00:13:26.151 --> 00:13:28.686
Sebastian: 7.62, lead ore.

00:13:28.720 --> 00:13:31.188
It's Russian,
but manufactured in Bulgaria.

00:13:31.206 --> 00:13:32.923
- Fairly rare.
<i>- Russian?</i>

00:13:33.532 --> 00:13:34.377
What's the case?

00:13:34.497 --> 00:13:35.857
<i>Kidnapping in Cannes.</i>

00:13:35.977 --> 00:13:37.534
The victim's called
Maxim Marianski.

00:13:37.654 --> 00:13:39.186
His father's
a Russian billionaire.

00:13:39.306 --> 00:13:42.165
Double-tap kills
are a military tactic.

00:13:42.199 --> 00:13:44.705
A lot of Russian
military went bad,

00:13:45.053 --> 00:13:46.103
and they don't like
the new rich.

00:13:46.137 --> 00:13:47.721
There could be
a connection there.

00:13:47.755 --> 00:13:49.122
Is that enough
to make it cross-border?

00:13:49.140 --> 00:13:51.308
To ask for the case?

00:13:51.342 --> 00:13:53.844
<i>The crime itself</i>
<i>is only within France...</i>

00:13:53.895 --> 00:13:54.811
<i>As far as we know.</i>

00:13:54.846 --> 00:13:57.964
But... we have
a similar Florence case.

00:13:59.400 --> 00:14:00.901
Oh, yeah.
I remember that.

00:14:00.935 --> 00:14:04.288
Rich victim,
blitz attack on security,

00:14:04.322 --> 00:14:07.407
double-tap kills
with 7.62s...

00:14:07.442 --> 00:14:09.026
Sure looks like
the same team did both.

00:14:09.060 --> 00:14:10.777
<i>I'll call Dorn.</i>

00:14:10.812 --> 00:14:12.079
<i>Sebastian, get your equipment.</i>

00:14:12.113 --> 00:14:14.264
<i>We are all going</i>
<i>to the South of France.</i>

00:14:14.299 --> 00:14:19.102
<i>Pick me up in a chopper</i>
<i>at the heliport. Bye.</i>

00:14:19.137 --> 00:14:21.821
Wow... a man asking me
to the South of France

00:14:21.839 --> 00:14:22.839
on a Saturday night?

00:14:22.874 --> 00:14:25.459
You would think
that would sound sexier.

00:14:25.493 --> 00:14:27.544
Anne-Marie and Hickman
were already there...

00:14:28.880 --> 00:14:30.847
Together.

00:14:30.882 --> 00:14:33.100
[Shocked chatter]

00:14:33.134 --> 00:14:34.218
Woman: Where is my son?

00:14:34.269 --> 00:14:36.326
I need to
speak to someone there!

00:14:36.446 --> 00:14:38.020
What's going on?

00:14:38.054 --> 00:14:40.489
- The victim's mother is here.
- I need to see my son!

00:14:40.524 --> 00:14:41.757
They let her
into the crime scene?

00:14:41.877 --> 00:14:42.928
You're gonna be in big trouble!

00:14:43.048 --> 00:14:45.611
In Cannes, no one refuses
Caroline Marianski anything.

00:14:45.731 --> 00:14:48.740
Hey! Please! Does anyone
know where my son is?

00:14:49.082 --> 00:14:50.266
Madame Marianski?

00:14:50.301 --> 00:14:51.584
Yes.

00:14:51.602 --> 00:14:53.052
- I'm Captain Geroux.
- Hi.

00:14:53.086 --> 00:14:55.355
Shall we find some privacy?

00:15:00.144 --> 00:15:02.395
Victim's father, Lev Marianski,

00:15:02.429 --> 00:15:04.429
is one of the richest men
in the world.

00:15:05.282 --> 00:15:06.899
He's just arrived.

00:15:06.933 --> 00:15:08.151
Where does his money come from?

00:15:08.202 --> 00:15:10.620
Well, initially, black market,
after the fall,

00:15:10.654 --> 00:15:13.156
but he went much more mainstream
in the last decade.

00:15:13.207 --> 00:15:15.958
He has tech companies,
financial companies,

00:15:15.993 --> 00:15:17.443
a string of high-end stores,

00:15:17.461 --> 00:15:19.379
even owns a football team
in Italy...

00:15:19.413 --> 00:15:22.548
A team that never covers
the point spread, by the way.

00:15:22.583 --> 00:15:24.617
Hickman:
<i>Soccer has a spread?</i>

00:15:24.635 --> 00:15:26.452
It's called "football."

00:15:26.470 --> 00:15:27.553
Hickman:
<i>Yeah, whatever it's called,</i>

00:15:27.588 --> 00:15:28.638
<i>how do you figure</i>
<i>a point spread in a game</i>

00:15:28.672 --> 00:15:30.390
where nobody ever
scores any points?

00:15:30.424 --> 00:15:33.309
Well, someone scores,
or I wouldn't have so ma...

00:15:34.511 --> 00:15:37.230
Anyway. We are 15 minutes out.

00:15:37.264 --> 00:15:38.481
Madame Marianski...

00:15:38.515 --> 00:15:39.515
It's Pelletier.

00:15:40.351 --> 00:15:41.967
We divorced three years ago,

00:15:41.985 --> 00:15:45.355
and I took back my maiden name
the moment I legally could.

00:15:45.406 --> 00:15:48.191
Who are you people again?

00:15:48.242 --> 00:15:49.108
We work out of

00:15:49.142 --> 00:15:50.910
the International
Criminal Court.

00:15:50.944 --> 00:15:53.312
Mrs. Marianski:
Handling kidnappings?

00:15:53.330 --> 00:15:54.497
Well, handling
cross-border crimes.

00:15:54.531 --> 00:15:56.282
I don't understand.

00:15:56.316 --> 00:15:57.667
They took him across a border?

00:15:57.701 --> 00:15:59.318
No, madame.

00:15:59.336 --> 00:16:01.654
There was a similar kidnapping
in Florence,

00:16:01.672 --> 00:16:03.189
several months ago.

00:16:03.223 --> 00:16:04.607
So this is
a professional group?

00:16:04.641 --> 00:16:05.625
The kidnappers?

00:16:05.659 --> 00:16:06.926
It appears so.

00:16:06.960 --> 00:16:08.511
All kidnappings are
professional, aren't they?

00:16:08.545 --> 00:16:11.180
Unless the parents do it.

00:16:11.215 --> 00:16:12.515
Look.

00:16:12.549 --> 00:16:15.968
If you want to investigate me,
investigate me.

00:16:16.002 --> 00:16:18.471
Until then, what are you
doing to find my son?

00:16:18.505 --> 00:16:20.356
Sir, look around you.

00:16:20.391 --> 00:16:22.975
Almost every officer
in the region is here.

00:16:23.009 --> 00:16:24.176
Standing around, doing nothing.

00:16:24.194 --> 00:16:25.461
In a ransom kidnapping,

00:16:25.496 --> 00:16:27.530
you generally need to wait
for further contact.

00:16:27.564 --> 00:16:29.515
How long will that take?

00:16:30.684 --> 00:16:32.568
You have somewhere
more important to be?

00:16:34.354 --> 00:16:36.706
You've checked your watch twice
since you got here.

00:16:36.740 --> 00:16:38.324
No. I have nowhere to be.

00:16:38.358 --> 00:16:39.475
How much time
do you have before

00:16:39.510 --> 00:16:41.160
you need to report this
to the insurance company?

00:16:41.194 --> 00:16:42.295
Insurance?

00:16:42.329 --> 00:16:44.530
Mr. Marianski,
you must insure your valuables?

00:16:44.548 --> 00:16:46.499
Did you buy an insurance
on Maxim?

00:16:46.533 --> 00:16:47.967
Caroline...

00:16:48.001 --> 00:16:49.385
Usually, a man
in your ex-husband's position

00:16:49.420 --> 00:16:52.422
takes out an insurance policy,
a kidnap policy, on his family.

00:16:52.473 --> 00:16:54.507
He probably has one
on you as well.

00:16:54.541 --> 00:16:56.215
Is that true?

00:16:58.211 --> 00:16:59.542
As you say, it was prudent.

00:16:59.662 --> 00:17:00.924
But we're not
married any longer.

00:17:01.044 --> 00:17:03.048
You can buy
insurance on anyone.

00:17:05.051 --> 00:17:06.052
You cold bastard.

00:17:07.254 --> 00:17:09.355
Actually, madame,
kidnap insurance

00:17:09.389 --> 00:17:10.723
provides certainty

00:17:10.741 --> 00:17:13.493
that, if something like this
should happen,

00:17:13.527 --> 00:17:15.111
the ransom money would be
readily available.

00:17:15.145 --> 00:17:18.030
Hickman: It also tends to
keep negotiations to a minimum.

00:17:18.064 --> 00:17:19.398
Makes it more of
a business transaction.

00:17:19.416 --> 00:17:22.568
You probably have a million
reasons to hate your ex-husband,

00:17:22.586 --> 00:17:25.004
but this shouldn't be
one of 'em.

00:17:25.038 --> 00:17:26.706
May I have a moment
with you, please?

00:17:35.549 --> 00:17:36.632
"Millions of reasons"
to hate me?

00:17:36.683 --> 00:17:39.018
Three years after a divorce,

00:17:39.052 --> 00:17:40.085
a rich ex-wife should have

00:17:40.103 --> 00:17:41.687
a string of young guys
helping her forget,

00:17:41.722 --> 00:17:43.606
but she's still
really pissed at you.

00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:45.024
That kind of anger is earned.

00:17:45.058 --> 00:17:47.460
Right now, I'm more
concerned about the chip.

00:17:47.494 --> 00:17:49.412
Chip?

00:17:49.446 --> 00:17:51.597
Your son has a tracer chip
in him, right?

00:17:51.615 --> 00:17:53.065
I wouldn't...

00:17:53.099 --> 00:17:54.099
Things are gonna go

00:17:54.117 --> 00:17:56.235
so much easier
if you don't lie to me.

00:17:56.270 --> 00:17:59.338
[♪]

00:18:01.291 --> 00:18:02.675
[Sighs reluctantly]

00:18:02.709 --> 00:18:04.043
You're wearing a $23,000 watch.

00:18:04.077 --> 00:18:06.712
So?

00:18:06.747 --> 00:18:09.048
It's a fake.
The sub-dial is all wrong.

00:18:09.082 --> 00:18:10.816
The inner wall should
be gold, not white.

00:18:10.851 --> 00:18:12.385
It's too thick by half.

00:18:12.419 --> 00:18:13.803
But it's a good fake,
it's a professional fake,

00:18:13.837 --> 00:18:15.371
and they don't
come cheap either,

00:18:15.405 --> 00:18:16.622
which suggests

00:18:16.640 --> 00:18:20.176
that you...
You like to look good,

00:18:20.227 --> 00:18:21.527
but you're not above
saving a buck.

00:18:21.562 --> 00:18:23.729
Kidnap insurance
gives a discount

00:18:23.764 --> 00:18:25.798
when the insured
has a locator chip,

00:18:25.816 --> 00:18:27.767
and I'm guessing that
you went for that option.

00:18:27.801 --> 00:18:29.569
[♪]

00:18:29.603 --> 00:18:30.570
She can't know.

00:18:30.604 --> 00:18:32.772
Oh, she most definitely
will know,

00:18:32.806 --> 00:18:34.273
but our problem right now

00:18:34.307 --> 00:18:36.192
is what the chip-makers
don't tell you.

00:18:36.243 --> 00:18:38.160
Hey! Hurry up, I said!

00:18:38.195 --> 00:18:39.478
Jacket! Now!

00:18:39.496 --> 00:18:41.146
Hickman: <i>These are probably</i>
<i>professional kidnappers.</i>

00:18:41.164 --> 00:18:43.482
<i>Knowing the level</i>
<i>of Maxim's security,</i>

00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:44.650
<i>they'll expect a chip, too.</i>

00:18:44.668 --> 00:18:45.785
<i>They'll get rid of</i>

00:18:45.819 --> 00:18:47.787
<i>every shred of clothing,</i>
<i>down to his skin.</i>

00:18:47.821 --> 00:18:49.655
<i>Then glasses, jewellery,</i>
<i>piercings, prosthetics...</i>

00:18:49.673 --> 00:18:53.292
<i>Anything removable</i>
<i>that could hide a device.</i>

00:18:53.326 --> 00:18:55.428
<i>Finally, when</i>
<i>he's completely stripped,</i>

00:18:55.462 --> 00:18:57.630
<i>they'll scan him</i>
<i>to check for any electronics.</i>

00:18:57.664 --> 00:18:59.682
<i>And they're going to find it.</i>

00:18:59.716 --> 00:19:00.883
<i>Question is...</i>

00:19:00.918 --> 00:19:02.852
Is the tracking device
something that he carries,

00:19:02.886 --> 00:19:04.554
or did you have it
implanted inside him?

00:19:11.469 --> 00:19:13.119
You put a tracking
device inside him?

00:19:13.153 --> 00:19:15.187
For his own protection.

00:19:15.205 --> 00:19:16.122
When did you do this?

00:19:16.156 --> 00:19:17.707
When he visited me in Minsk.

00:19:17.741 --> 00:19:19.659
A Russian doctor
cut open our son?

00:19:19.693 --> 00:19:23.212
It was probably
more like an injection.

00:19:23.246 --> 00:19:24.246
What kind of monster does that?

00:19:24.298 --> 00:19:25.715
I'm a monster
for wanting him safe?

00:19:25.749 --> 00:19:28.167
They only thing you wanted
is to save money!

00:19:28.201 --> 00:19:29.552
You mean like hiring

00:19:29.586 --> 00:19:32.555
those useless
French security men?

00:19:32.589 --> 00:19:34.140
Better than
the gorillas you use.

00:19:34.174 --> 00:19:36.008
I can see how much
better your people are.

00:19:36.042 --> 00:19:36.842
All right, while
watching you two

00:19:36.876 --> 00:19:38.010
has been thoroughly enjoyable,

00:19:38.044 --> 00:19:40.146
why don't we start
focusing on your son?

00:19:40.180 --> 00:19:42.398
What will they do if they
find it, the tracking device?

00:19:42.432 --> 00:19:45.050
I don't know.
It's hard to tell at this point.

00:19:45.068 --> 00:19:47.687
- Well, tell me the truth!
- The truth about what?

00:19:50.774 --> 00:19:52.441
We have four dead
on the first floor.

00:19:52.492 --> 00:19:53.442
Do you mind checking it out?

00:19:53.477 --> 00:19:54.443
Yeah, sure.

00:19:54.494 --> 00:19:55.995
The victim
has a tracer implant.

00:19:56.029 --> 00:19:58.197
- Do we know the tag I.D.?
- I have it.

00:19:59.282 --> 00:20:00.333
[Mutters]

00:20:00.367 --> 00:20:03.452
Just give me
a second to set up.

00:20:03.503 --> 00:20:05.705
[♪]

00:20:06.623 --> 00:20:09.091
These wankers are efficient.

00:20:10.794 --> 00:20:14.413
Four dead, eight shots.

00:20:14.448 --> 00:20:15.414
Clean...

00:20:15.449 --> 00:20:16.515
Cold.

00:20:16.550 --> 00:20:17.583
Bodyguard.

00:20:17.601 --> 00:20:18.467
[Shot fires]

00:20:18.518 --> 00:20:19.552
Bouncer.

00:20:19.586 --> 00:20:20.553
[Firing]

00:20:20.587 --> 00:20:21.754
Bodyguard.

00:20:21.772 --> 00:20:23.222
[Shot echoes]

00:20:23.256 --> 00:20:25.141
Who's the girl?

00:20:25.192 --> 00:20:26.425
[Fires]

00:20:26.443 --> 00:20:29.145
She looks like a civilian.

00:20:29.196 --> 00:20:33.115
Maybe she was with the target.

00:20:35.652 --> 00:20:36.702
[Maxim wails]
Why did you kill her?

00:20:36.737 --> 00:20:39.572
Man: Shut up.

00:20:39.606 --> 00:20:41.624
[Maxim sobs quietly]

00:20:41.658 --> 00:20:44.243
[♪]

00:20:47.297 --> 00:20:48.113
Do we know who that girl was,

00:20:48.131 --> 00:20:49.248
the one they shot?

00:20:49.282 --> 00:20:50.249
She was called Laure.

00:20:50.283 --> 00:20:52.134
Maxim's girlfriend.

00:20:52.169 --> 00:20:54.220
How long had
they been together?

00:20:54.254 --> 00:20:55.287
Six months.

00:20:55.305 --> 00:20:56.589
She was a gold-digger
from the <i>Banlieue.</i>

00:20:56.623 --> 00:20:57.923
How do you know that?

00:20:57.957 --> 00:21:00.342
She hates all his girlfriends,
since he was 10 years old.

00:21:00.394 --> 00:21:04.563
Why else would a 28-year-old
be dating a teenager?

00:21:04.598 --> 00:21:06.515
He'll be 20 next week
and he's in love with her.

00:21:06.566 --> 00:21:08.601
Oh, stop.
At that age,

00:21:08.635 --> 00:21:10.436
boys are in love
with every girl.

00:21:10.470 --> 00:21:12.738
I have it...
The tracking device.

00:21:12.773 --> 00:21:13.572
Is it moving?

00:21:13.607 --> 00:21:15.808
Doesn't seem to be.

00:21:15.826 --> 00:21:16.742
Can you get a location?

00:21:16.777 --> 00:21:18.527
Yep. It's at...

00:21:18.578 --> 00:21:21.747
Avenue Beauregard in Cannes.

00:21:21.782 --> 00:21:22.581
Are you sure?

00:21:22.616 --> 00:21:24.116
What does that mean to you?

00:21:24.150 --> 00:21:25.818
It's our...

00:21:25.836 --> 00:21:28.254
Her address.

00:21:28.288 --> 00:21:29.588
The family villa.

00:21:29.623 --> 00:21:31.257
He's at home?

00:21:31.291 --> 00:21:33.626
[♪]

00:21:42.803 --> 00:21:44.136
Hickman: Don't touch that.

00:21:44.170 --> 00:21:45.838
Please.

00:21:45.856 --> 00:21:47.890
[♪]

00:21:55.615 --> 00:21:56.482
"We will
contact you soon."

00:21:56.516 --> 00:21:57.516
[♪]

00:21:57.534 --> 00:21:58.701
What is that?

00:22:00.537 --> 00:22:02.488
It's a microch.

00:22:05.876 --> 00:22:08.160
[♪]

00:22:12.249 --> 00:22:14.500
Is there any indication
of time on the note?

00:22:14.534 --> 00:22:16.368
Only "soon."

00:22:16.386 --> 00:22:18.137
Where was the device
implanted in him?

00:22:18.171 --> 00:22:19.371
Back of the hand.

00:22:19.389 --> 00:22:21.590
Probably not a critical injury.

00:22:21.641 --> 00:22:22.842
Hickman:
Hand ain't no picnic.

00:22:22.876 --> 00:22:24.894
- Well... oh, I didn't mean...
- I'm just busting balls.

00:22:27.347 --> 00:22:28.213
Messing around.

00:22:28.231 --> 00:22:31.150
So, Sebastian,
set up in the house

00:22:31.184 --> 00:22:32.768
to trap and trace
any ransom call.

00:22:32.819 --> 00:22:34.720
I'll also capture
the data lines,

00:22:34.738 --> 00:22:35.721
in case
they reach out digitally.

00:22:35.739 --> 00:22:36.906
Good.

00:22:36.940 --> 00:22:38.724
Poke around
the family financial records.

00:22:40.560 --> 00:22:41.610
We may need them.

00:22:41.661 --> 00:22:42.895
Wouldn't that be illegal?

00:22:42.913 --> 00:22:45.498
We're not trying to
prosecute him for anything.

00:22:45.532 --> 00:22:46.866
Not yet.

00:22:47.918 --> 00:22:49.451
What do you need from me?

00:22:49.503 --> 00:22:51.187
There was an advance guard,

00:22:51.221 --> 00:22:52.221
who was not present

00:22:52.255 --> 00:22:53.439
when the kidnapping took place.

00:22:53.473 --> 00:22:55.875
Maybe it was an inside job.

00:22:55.909 --> 00:22:56.675
Right.

00:22:58.929 --> 00:23:00.546
Eva, I need you in Florence.

00:23:00.580 --> 00:23:03.415
Maybe there's something
from the other kidnapping

00:23:03.433 --> 00:23:04.266
that can help us here.

00:23:04.301 --> 00:23:06.418
Okay.

00:23:06.436 --> 00:23:08.637
Anne-Marie...

00:23:08.688 --> 00:23:10.523
This is our base of operations.

00:23:10.557 --> 00:23:11.857
Liaise with the parents.

00:23:11.892 --> 00:23:12.858
Excuse me, sir?

00:23:12.893 --> 00:23:15.728
Explain that, now,
it's a waiting game.

00:23:15.762 --> 00:23:18.731
We wait for the kidnappers
to contact us,

00:23:18.765 --> 00:23:20.432
then get
the insurance company involved.

00:23:20.450 --> 00:23:21.784
Yeah. Uh...

00:23:21.818 --> 00:23:23.569
Sir, I'm really sorry, but...
[Forced laugh]

00:23:23.603 --> 00:23:25.604
almost anyone else
is better-suited than me...

00:23:25.622 --> 00:23:27.289
- ...to take care of...
- You can do it.

00:23:28.325 --> 00:23:29.291
You can.

00:23:32.996 --> 00:23:35.331
Mrs. Marianski: No, I'm not
listening to you anymore!

00:23:35.365 --> 00:23:37.333
This is all your fault.

00:23:37.384 --> 00:23:38.551
How is it my fault?

00:23:38.585 --> 00:23:40.586
If you spent more time
thinking of him...

00:23:40.620 --> 00:23:43.222
That is one seriously
dysfunctional divorce.

00:23:43.256 --> 00:23:44.974
[Quietly] Please, Carl...

00:23:45.008 --> 00:23:47.643
Their child is in danger.

00:23:49.679 --> 00:23:53.399
[♪]

00:24:18.541 --> 00:24:20.459
[Maxim pants in fear]

00:24:22.512 --> 00:24:24.263
Step, step, step.

00:24:24.297 --> 00:24:25.681
Get down.

00:24:25.715 --> 00:24:26.882
[He whimpers]

00:24:26.933 --> 00:24:29.301
[♪]

00:24:32.889 --> 00:24:35.357
[Shackles clattering]

00:24:40.647 --> 00:24:41.697
[Lock shifts and clatters]

00:24:41.731 --> 00:24:44.817
[Panting]

00:24:47.704 --> 00:24:49.655
[Grunting]

00:24:49.689 --> 00:24:52.041
[♪]

00:24:59.532 --> 00:25:00.833
[Gunshot echoing]

00:25:00.867 --> 00:25:03.802
[♪]

00:25:06.506 --> 00:25:08.924
[Footsteps]

00:25:24.441 --> 00:25:29.411
[Sobbing]

00:25:38.881 --> 00:25:40.599
Madame Pelletier?

00:25:40.633 --> 00:25:42.250
Is there news?

00:25:42.285 --> 00:25:43.718
No, no, no. Um...

00:25:43.769 --> 00:25:45.804
I...

00:25:45.838 --> 00:25:47.005
I'm very sorry

00:25:47.039 --> 00:25:49.307
that this is happening
to you, madame.

00:25:51.627 --> 00:25:53.344
Would you care for some tea?

00:25:53.362 --> 00:25:55.931
I... I can do that!

00:25:55.965 --> 00:25:56.982
I'll do that.

00:25:59.785 --> 00:26:01.703
[♪]

00:26:03.039 --> 00:26:05.123
[Exhales] Now... let's see
what you've been up to,

00:26:05.158 --> 00:26:07.209
Mr. Marianski.

00:26:07.243 --> 00:26:08.743
[Punches a key]

00:26:08.794 --> 00:26:11.713
[♪]

00:26:21.390 --> 00:26:23.391
[Knocking]

00:26:26.128 --> 00:26:28.230
[♪]

00:26:30.766 --> 00:26:33.051
Tommy: I can have a mate
who can enhance all this, so...

00:26:33.069 --> 00:26:35.053
Maybe he'll get
something out of it.

00:26:35.087 --> 00:26:36.821
I'll copy it for you.

00:26:38.641 --> 00:26:39.698
You're...

00:26:39.818 --> 00:26:42.327
All from the International
Criminal Court?

00:26:42.361 --> 00:26:44.279
Yeah. Sort of.

00:26:44.679 --> 00:26:48.333
We, uh, specialize
in cross-border crime.

00:26:48.367 --> 00:26:50.869
These kidnappers may have
done another one in Florence.

00:26:50.903 --> 00:26:53.705
Professional kidnappers don't
usually kill anyone, do they?

00:26:53.739 --> 00:26:55.824
Not unless they have to.

00:26:55.858 --> 00:26:57.709
It's bad for business.

00:26:57.743 --> 00:26:59.744
So how long have you

00:26:59.762 --> 00:27:02.080
worked for the family?

00:27:02.114 --> 00:27:03.965
Six months.

00:27:04.016 --> 00:27:05.893
We don't work for the family,
by the way.

00:27:06.013 --> 00:27:07.519
No?

00:27:07.587 --> 00:27:09.538
Madame Pelletier is the client.

00:27:09.589 --> 00:27:12.424
The father doesn't trust us.

00:27:12.459 --> 00:27:13.825
What about Maxim?

00:27:13.843 --> 00:27:16.495
Maxim...

00:27:16.529 --> 00:27:17.630
He's a security nightmare.

00:27:17.664 --> 00:27:20.232
Always taking off,

00:27:20.266 --> 00:27:22.801
trying to shake off
his bodyguards.

00:27:22.835 --> 00:27:24.836
These kidnappers...

00:27:24.854 --> 00:27:26.639
They didn't wait
till he was alone.

00:27:26.673 --> 00:27:28.774
Yeah.

00:27:28.808 --> 00:27:29.775
Probably because

00:27:29.809 --> 00:27:31.810
of Laure.

00:27:31.845 --> 00:27:34.363
The girlfriend.

00:27:34.397 --> 00:27:36.482
He was very protective of her.

00:27:39.436 --> 00:27:41.170
Is there something
you want to say about her?

00:27:41.204 --> 00:27:43.238
She was the one
who wanted to go.

00:27:43.289 --> 00:27:44.673
To the club?

00:27:44.708 --> 00:27:46.275
And to the party.

00:27:48.161 --> 00:27:49.628
The non-existent
party.

00:27:49.663 --> 00:27:50.896
Yeah.

00:27:50.930 --> 00:27:54.383
That's why Jacques only had
one guard with him.

00:27:56.869 --> 00:27:59.838
I'm sorry about your boss.

00:27:59.873 --> 00:28:02.558
He was a good man.

00:28:04.661 --> 00:28:06.478
Good bodyguard.

00:28:10.350 --> 00:28:11.550
Have you ever lost a partner?

00:28:13.886 --> 00:28:15.771
Uh, yeah.

00:28:15.822 --> 00:28:17.523
And...

00:28:17.557 --> 00:28:19.658
how do you handle the guilt?

00:28:22.662 --> 00:28:25.364
I figure that out,
I'll let you know.

00:28:28.718 --> 00:28:33.405
[♪]

00:28:36.943 --> 00:28:40.029
We'll make the video,
then I'll call Katya.

00:28:43.016 --> 00:28:44.367
Hey, hey.

00:28:44.401 --> 00:28:46.852
That can wait
'til after the video.

00:28:46.870 --> 00:28:48.321
He must be starving.

00:28:48.355 --> 00:28:49.121
So?

00:28:52.742 --> 00:28:54.526
We can do the video
after he eats.

00:28:54.544 --> 00:28:57.546
What? Are you soft for him?

00:28:57.580 --> 00:28:58.864
Don't be stupid.

00:28:58.882 --> 00:29:00.299
Then what's troubling you?

00:29:00.333 --> 00:29:03.034
This. The whole thing.

00:29:03.052 --> 00:29:04.920
I don't...

00:29:06.973 --> 00:29:07.673
It feels wrong.

00:29:09.092 --> 00:29:11.376
Hey.

00:29:12.545 --> 00:29:14.012
This is our biggest one.

00:29:14.047 --> 00:29:16.732
Huh? Ever.

00:29:16.766 --> 00:29:19.351
After that, we'll stop, huh?

00:29:19.385 --> 00:29:22.721
Like we always wanted.

00:29:28.661 --> 00:29:29.778
Put your mask back on.

00:29:29.829 --> 00:29:31.830
I'm not an idiot, Yan.

00:29:37.670 --> 00:29:39.421
Here, some food.

00:29:39.455 --> 00:29:40.756
I don't want any.

00:29:40.790 --> 00:29:42.040
You have to eat.

00:29:42.075 --> 00:29:44.793
After we make the ransom video,
your father will pay,

00:29:44.844 --> 00:29:46.378
then you can go home.

00:29:46.412 --> 00:29:49.998
He isn't going to
pay anything for me.

00:29:50.033 --> 00:29:50.916
He will.

00:29:50.950 --> 00:29:52.601
Then you can go home.

00:29:52.635 --> 00:29:55.053
Home to what?

00:29:58.057 --> 00:29:59.641
[♪]

00:29:59.692 --> 00:30:02.644
[Door locks, bolt clatters]

00:30:08.534 --> 00:30:11.403
[Computer beeps]

00:30:12.572 --> 00:30:14.373
Come on.
Come on, come on, come on.

00:30:14.407 --> 00:30:15.407
[Exhales in annoyance]

00:30:15.441 --> 00:30:19.561
[Mutters under her breath]

00:30:19.596 --> 00:30:22.164
[Cell ringing]

00:30:23.166 --> 00:30:24.383
Eva?

00:30:24.417 --> 00:30:27.703
I'm trying to link Maxim
with the Florence victim.

00:30:27.737 --> 00:30:30.906
<i>They are both teenagers</i>
<i>with very rich parents,</i>

00:30:30.940 --> 00:30:34.142
<i>but different cities,</i>
<i>different nationalities,</i>

00:30:34.177 --> 00:30:35.844
<i>and with different profiles.</i>

00:30:35.878 --> 00:30:37.112
<i>So, Allesandro,</i>
<i>the boy in Florence,</i>

00:30:37.146 --> 00:30:39.965
he appears to be
a motivated art student

00:30:39.983 --> 00:30:42.067
at the Centro di Restauro,

00:30:42.101 --> 00:30:43.402
<i>but Maxim...</i>

00:30:43.436 --> 00:30:44.686
Is your typical
trust-fund waster.

00:30:44.737 --> 00:30:46.471
"Waster?"

00:30:46.489 --> 00:30:47.689
You sound like Tommy.

00:30:47.740 --> 00:30:48.941
I guess I'm not any happier

00:30:48.975 --> 00:30:50.943
with people
who have too much money.

00:30:50.977 --> 00:30:52.995
<i>How much is too much?</i>

00:30:53.029 --> 00:30:54.696
Eva...

00:30:54.747 --> 00:30:58.450
Do the guys know each other?

00:30:58.484 --> 00:31:00.118
Okay. Um... no.

00:31:00.152 --> 00:31:02.504
There's no evidence
they've ever met.

00:31:02.538 --> 00:31:03.872
All right, how can I help?

00:31:03.923 --> 00:31:06.491
Well, part of the Florence file
is available,

00:31:06.509 --> 00:31:07.509
but the other part is locked,

00:31:07.543 --> 00:31:09.628
<i>so I don't know how to get in.</i>

00:31:09.662 --> 00:31:11.580
I think I can get into it
by the time you get to Florence.

00:31:11.614 --> 00:31:14.933
Okay. Well, I think
I'll be there in about...

00:31:14.968 --> 00:31:16.001
42 minutes.

00:31:16.019 --> 00:31:17.602
I've got your progress
on my screen.

00:31:17.637 --> 00:31:19.454
Okay, then. Thanks. <i>Grazie.</i>

00:31:19.489 --> 00:31:20.555
<i>Ciao, ciao.</i>

00:31:20.606 --> 00:31:21.940
Okay.

00:31:21.975 --> 00:31:23.558
How much are you into them for?

00:31:23.609 --> 00:31:24.476
[♪]

00:31:34.487 --> 00:31:35.854
I had a partner who gambled.

00:31:35.872 --> 00:31:37.689
The only time
he talked about it

00:31:37.707 --> 00:31:38.907
was when he was winning big

00:31:38.958 --> 00:31:42.577
or losing big.

00:31:42.628 --> 00:31:43.996
And...

00:31:44.030 --> 00:31:45.497
no offense, but...

00:31:45.531 --> 00:31:47.082
you don't seem like a guy
on a winning streak.

00:31:48.701 --> 00:31:49.835
[Laughs]

00:31:49.869 --> 00:31:51.003
Why is "no offense"

00:31:51.037 --> 00:31:53.505
always followed by
something entirely offensive?

00:31:56.242 --> 00:31:57.893
I am not into anybody
for anything.

00:32:02.982 --> 00:32:04.182
All right...

00:32:04.216 --> 00:32:07.269
[♪]

00:32:12.075 --> 00:32:13.759
[♪]

00:32:31.127 --> 00:32:34.746
[♪]

00:32:59.739 --> 00:33:02.624
[Cell begins ringing]

00:33:03.743 --> 00:33:04.743
Hello, Dorn.

00:33:04.777 --> 00:33:06.578
What are you doing, Louis?

00:33:06.612 --> 00:33:08.914
I am on a case.

00:33:08.948 --> 00:33:10.132
Did you think I wouldn't know?

00:33:10.166 --> 00:33:13.218
Know? What do you mean, know?
Know what?

00:33:13.252 --> 00:33:15.303
I have alerts everywhere.

00:33:15.338 --> 00:33:17.305
What are you
talking about, Dorn?

00:33:17.340 --> 00:33:20.175
The Russian, Louis!

00:33:20.226 --> 00:33:23.745
You said I could handle it
without interference.

00:33:25.031 --> 00:33:25.947
I have.

00:33:25.998 --> 00:33:28.700
You're running checks
on my source.

00:33:28.734 --> 00:33:30.619
<i>No.</i>

00:33:30.670 --> 00:33:31.703
Yes, you are.

00:33:31.737 --> 00:33:35.791
I just told you...
I have alerts in the files.

00:33:35.842 --> 00:33:39.077
Someone is going through
the financial records

00:33:39.095 --> 00:33:41.213
<i>of the man</i>
<i>who gave me Dimitrov.</i>

00:33:41.247 --> 00:33:42.881
<i>Someone with</i>

00:33:42.915 --> 00:33:46.635
I.C.C. authorization
is trailing him.

00:33:46.686 --> 00:33:48.854
<i>Are you going to</i>
<i>try to tell me that</i>

00:33:48.888 --> 00:33:53.258
it isn't you or...
your German computer whiz?

00:33:54.777 --> 00:33:56.728
Your source, what's his name?

00:33:56.762 --> 00:33:58.980
[Dorn scoffs] What do you mean?

00:33:59.031 --> 00:34:00.982
[Mimics louis]
"What is his name?"

00:34:01.033 --> 00:34:02.818
Marianski?

00:34:02.852 --> 00:34:04.686
It's Lev Marianski?

00:34:04.720 --> 00:34:06.938
Why do you ask me?

00:34:07.619 --> 00:34:11.860
Because I'm standing
in his son's room.

00:34:11.911 --> 00:34:14.312
[♪]

00:34:16.815 --> 00:34:19.968
The kidnapping case...

00:34:20.002 --> 00:34:22.287
it is Marianski's son?

00:34:22.321 --> 00:34:25.257
Yeah. And we think
the kidnappers are Russian,

00:34:25.291 --> 00:34:28.176
and they used military tactics.

00:34:28.211 --> 00:34:32.714
It is of utmost importance that
you keep me informed, Louis.

00:34:32.748 --> 00:34:35.884
I must know
if Dimitrov is involved.

00:34:35.935 --> 00:34:39.037
<i>If I were to go to Russia,</i>

00:34:39.071 --> 00:34:42.023
I would never make it back.

00:34:42.058 --> 00:34:45.744
[♪]

00:34:49.415 --> 00:34:53.351
[♪]

00:34:57.640 --> 00:34:58.740
<i>[Flashback] Max...</i>

00:34:58.791 --> 00:35:01.910
<i>[She laughs]</i>

00:35:01.961 --> 00:35:03.194
<i>[Shutter clicks]</i>

00:35:05.998 --> 00:35:08.166
[♪]

00:35:08.200 --> 00:35:09.701
[Gunshot echoing]

00:35:12.204 --> 00:35:13.672
Time to make a movie!

00:35:13.706 --> 00:35:15.373
- Why?
- I told you.

00:35:15.391 --> 00:35:17.208
For the ransom,
so you can go home.

00:35:20.045 --> 00:35:21.179
Why did you kill her?

00:35:21.213 --> 00:35:23.765
You did that.
You killed Laure.

00:35:23.816 --> 00:35:24.766
[Loud smacking sound,
Maxim cries out]

00:35:24.817 --> 00:35:25.767
It's okay, he didn't hurt me.

00:35:25.818 --> 00:35:27.402
You stay out of this.

00:35:30.239 --> 00:35:31.356
You touch her again...

00:35:31.390 --> 00:35:34.225
And we won't be needing
a video. Understand?

00:35:36.279 --> 00:35:37.895
You think I'm afraid of you?

00:35:37.914 --> 00:35:39.414
I told her...

00:35:39.448 --> 00:35:42.334
My father isn't going to pay
to get me back.

00:35:42.368 --> 00:35:43.835
He hates me.

00:35:43.869 --> 00:35:45.903
Just say what
I tell you to say.

00:35:47.423 --> 00:35:48.423
No.

00:35:48.457 --> 00:35:50.425
[♪]

00:35:54.046 --> 00:35:55.714
Then I'll kill your mother.

00:35:55.748 --> 00:35:57.132
[♪]

00:36:01.841 --> 00:36:03.581
After the divorce,

00:36:03.701 --> 00:36:05.505
we used to sit here,

00:36:05.523 --> 00:36:07.891
having tea together
in the morning,

00:36:07.942 --> 00:36:09.443
Maxim and me.

00:36:09.477 --> 00:36:10.777
That must've been nice.

00:36:10.812 --> 00:36:11.945
Nice?

00:36:11.980 --> 00:36:15.649
Do you know what they talked
about the entire time?

00:36:15.683 --> 00:36:17.451
While they were having their...

00:36:17.485 --> 00:36:18.535
Their "nice" tea?

00:36:18.570 --> 00:36:20.153
About me.

00:36:20.187 --> 00:36:21.488
Don't flatter yourself.

00:36:21.522 --> 00:36:23.073
Tell her all the things

00:36:23.124 --> 00:36:25.742
you told a teenage boy...
<i>a teenage boy...</i>

00:36:25.793 --> 00:36:27.044
About his father.

00:36:27.078 --> 00:36:28.579
I really don't need to know.

00:36:28.630 --> 00:36:29.463
She told him...

00:36:29.497 --> 00:36:30.631
I slept around,

00:36:30.665 --> 00:36:32.666
that I brought diseases home,

00:36:32.700 --> 00:36:34.751
that I fathered other children,

00:36:34.802 --> 00:36:36.536
that I never cared about them.

00:36:36.554 --> 00:36:37.921
What part of that is not true?

00:36:37.972 --> 00:36:39.673
A boy needs to
look up to his father.

00:36:39.707 --> 00:36:41.892
You poisoned him about me.

00:36:41.926 --> 00:36:43.577
To make your...
yourself feel better,

00:36:43.611 --> 00:36:45.062
to control him.

00:36:45.096 --> 00:36:46.096
Like you control him
with money?

00:36:46.147 --> 00:36:47.848
While you let him
squander all yours.

00:36:47.882 --> 00:36:49.116
Because you cut off
his support.

00:36:49.150 --> 00:36:52.218
I only had to support him
until he was 18 or in school.

00:36:52.236 --> 00:36:53.887
He's neither.

00:36:53.905 --> 00:36:55.155
Such a cheap bastard!

00:36:55.189 --> 00:36:56.222
He does nothing!

00:36:56.240 --> 00:36:58.492
Won't work!
Won't study!

00:36:58.526 --> 00:36:59.409
My cutting him off

00:36:59.444 --> 00:37:02.162
will finally make him
act like a man.

00:37:02.196 --> 00:37:03.080
That's enough!

00:37:03.114 --> 00:37:05.032
What are you doing?

00:37:06.534 --> 00:37:07.734
This is a game?

00:37:07.752 --> 00:37:08.952
[♪]

00:37:09.003 --> 00:37:13.240
You know, a lot of people
would love to have a child,

00:37:13.274 --> 00:37:16.242
and all you do is...

00:37:16.260 --> 00:37:18.495
Use him to hurt each other?

00:37:18.529 --> 00:37:19.963
No, we don't.

00:37:24.218 --> 00:37:25.085
We are under stress.

00:37:25.103 --> 00:37:26.687
Okay. Yeah.

00:37:26.721 --> 00:37:28.522
"Stress."

00:37:28.556 --> 00:37:29.640
Anne-Marie?

00:37:29.691 --> 00:37:31.558
We're meeting on the terrace.

00:37:38.733 --> 00:37:40.117
I suggest

00:37:40.151 --> 00:37:42.869
you find somewhere to sit...

00:37:42.904 --> 00:37:44.538
and think.

00:37:44.572 --> 00:37:46.189
Separately.

00:37:47.825 --> 00:37:49.993
Okay?

00:37:50.044 --> 00:37:52.212
[♪]

00:37:56.167 --> 00:37:58.051
[Computer beeps]

00:37:58.086 --> 00:37:59.920
[♪]

00:38:07.095 --> 00:38:09.012
[Ringing]

00:38:09.063 --> 00:38:10.097
Hello?

00:38:10.131 --> 00:38:11.798
You didn't tell the Italians

00:38:11.816 --> 00:38:12.799
about me going into
their files, did you?

00:38:12.817 --> 00:38:14.101
Excuse me?

00:38:14.135 --> 00:38:16.053
Well, I remember you saying
you were going to tell them

00:38:16.087 --> 00:38:17.320
to run a check-up
on their systems.

00:38:17.355 --> 00:38:20.574
Yeah. I...
I remember that.

00:38:20.608 --> 00:38:21.808
I was just kidding.

00:38:21.843 --> 00:38:24.144
Yeah, I tried to access
a Trojan Horse I installed,

00:38:24.162 --> 00:38:26.613
<i>but it seems closed.</i>

00:38:26.647 --> 00:38:28.031
Well, I wouldn't tell them,
okay?

00:38:28.082 --> 00:38:29.032
Well...

00:38:29.083 --> 00:38:30.584
whatever it is in that file,

00:38:30.618 --> 00:38:32.753
Florence really wants it secret.

00:38:34.338 --> 00:38:35.589
I have the address
of a witness,

00:38:35.623 --> 00:38:38.625
so I might just ask
how it all got solved.

00:38:38.659 --> 00:38:40.210
All right.
I'll be here if you need me.

00:38:40.261 --> 00:38:42.328
Eva: <i>Okay. Thank you.</i>

00:38:42.346 --> 00:38:43.964
Ciao.

00:38:45.767 --> 00:38:48.018
[Mutters to self]
Dammit.

00:38:48.052 --> 00:38:49.052
[Thumps phone down]

00:38:49.103 --> 00:38:50.721
Something wrong, mate?

00:38:50.772 --> 00:38:52.105
No. Nothing.

00:38:52.140 --> 00:38:53.640
Yeah, well,
Louis has called us together.

00:38:55.226 --> 00:38:57.227
Coming.

00:38:58.980 --> 00:39:00.346
<i>Uploading the video...</i>

00:39:00.364 --> 00:39:03.150
Now.

00:39:03.184 --> 00:39:05.118
[♪]

00:39:08.689 --> 00:39:10.273
I have the file.

00:39:10.308 --> 00:39:12.075
<i>This is the message...</i>

00:39:12.126 --> 00:39:16.263
<i>"10 million Euros in cash,</i>
<i>by 6:00 tonight.</i>

00:39:16.297 --> 00:39:18.048
<i>Delivery instructions</i>
<i>will follow."</i>

00:39:18.082 --> 00:39:19.800
I thought it was five million?

00:39:19.834 --> 00:39:21.134
The price has doubled.

00:39:21.169 --> 00:39:22.564
<i>Why?</i>

00:39:22.684 --> 00:39:24.971
Because I am in charge.

00:39:25.006 --> 00:39:26.973
What do you mean,
you're in charge?

00:39:27.008 --> 00:39:30.043
Just tell them, Katya!

00:39:30.061 --> 00:39:32.212
10 million.

00:39:32.230 --> 00:39:35.682
[♪]

00:39:35.716 --> 00:39:39.186
You think the girlfriend
set Maxim up for the kidnapping?

00:39:39.220 --> 00:39:40.253
She sent the advance team

00:39:40.288 --> 00:39:41.955
to a non-existent
party

00:39:41.989 --> 00:39:43.990
and she planned the trip
to the nightclub.

00:39:44.025 --> 00:39:46.176
Seems kind of
short-sighted of her.

00:39:46.210 --> 00:39:47.277
He's her boyfriend,

00:39:47.311 --> 00:39:49.396
and apparently,
he's worth millions.

00:39:49.430 --> 00:39:51.248
Well, his father
just cut his support.

00:39:51.282 --> 00:39:52.666
Really?

00:39:52.700 --> 00:39:53.817
So, what? Maxim was broke?

00:39:53.851 --> 00:39:55.702
Rich-kid "broke."

00:39:55.736 --> 00:39:57.003
He had a driver, a bodyguard
and a limo.

00:39:57.038 --> 00:39:59.089
Which were all
about to be taken away.

00:39:59.123 --> 00:40:01.124
Maybe he's in on it?

00:40:01.175 --> 00:40:04.044
I doubt he had a part
in killing the girlfriend.

00:40:04.078 --> 00:40:05.245
Security said
his whole lifestyle changed

00:40:05.263 --> 00:40:06.296
when he met her,

00:40:06.347 --> 00:40:08.431
became more... responsible.

00:40:08.466 --> 00:40:10.217
Maybe the kidnappers
killed Laure

00:40:10.251 --> 00:40:11.417
just because she was a witness?

00:40:11.435 --> 00:40:13.353
Not the first time.

00:40:13.387 --> 00:40:15.021
Okay, so, we dig into
the girlfriend's life

00:40:15.056 --> 00:40:18.424
and see if her contacts
give us a name.

00:40:18.442 --> 00:40:19.442
There's something
else about Marianski.

00:40:19.477 --> 00:40:20.443
What?

00:40:20.478 --> 00:40:22.896
He doesn't have
insurance on Maxim.

00:40:22.930 --> 00:40:24.965
Not anymore.

00:40:24.999 --> 00:40:27.083
And, for him,
he's short on cash.

00:40:27.118 --> 00:40:31.437
Most of his money is tied up
in investments and property,

00:40:31.455 --> 00:40:32.572
but he's only got

00:40:32.606 --> 00:40:33.406
a little more than 10 million
in liquid funds.

00:40:33.440 --> 00:40:35.375
He cancelled the policy?

00:40:35.409 --> 00:40:37.093
Yeah. About six months ago.

00:40:37.128 --> 00:40:38.161
What?

00:40:38.212 --> 00:40:40.113
[Footsteps]

00:40:41.415 --> 00:40:43.783
You went into my records?

00:40:45.469 --> 00:40:47.387
Did you cancel the insurance?

00:40:47.421 --> 00:40:48.839
You were angry
I even bought it.

00:40:48.890 --> 00:40:49.973
[Skype alert pings]

00:40:50.007 --> 00:40:52.475
That's our Skype call.

00:40:52.510 --> 00:40:54.811
[Alert continues pinging]

00:40:55.796 --> 00:40:58.131
It's coming in
on the family account.

00:40:58.149 --> 00:40:59.900
Mr. Marianski,
get in the chair.

00:41:02.069 --> 00:41:04.271
Hickman:
The important thing is to not

00:41:04.305 --> 00:41:06.022
let them think
that there's a problem.

00:41:06.073 --> 00:41:07.774
Just listen to the demand,

00:41:07.808 --> 00:41:08.825
and we'll figure it out later,
all right?

00:41:10.361 --> 00:41:11.862
Are you ready, Sebastian?

00:41:11.913 --> 00:41:13.179
[Computer beeps]

00:41:13.214 --> 00:41:14.164
Recording.

00:41:14.198 --> 00:41:15.448
[Skype keeps pinging]

00:41:15.482 --> 00:41:18.118
Answer it.

00:41:20.788 --> 00:41:21.972
[Hits key]

00:41:22.006 --> 00:41:23.290
<i>Maman?</i>

00:41:23.324 --> 00:41:24.490
Oh, God!

00:41:24.508 --> 00:41:27.043
Maxim: <i>Please pay.</i>
<i>These people have killed.</i>

00:41:27.094 --> 00:41:28.828
<i>They will hurt me.</i>

00:41:28.846 --> 00:41:30.513
[Scrambled voice]
The ransom is 10 million Euros,

00:41:30.548 --> 00:41:32.482
<i>by 6:00 P.M. tonight.</i>

00:41:32.516 --> 00:41:34.251
[♪]

00:41:37.104 --> 00:41:38.538
But...

00:41:38.573 --> 00:41:39.773
The insurance lapsed.

00:41:39.807 --> 00:41:41.191
I need more time.

00:41:41.225 --> 00:41:42.442
[Scrambled voice] <i>6:00 P.M.</i>

00:41:42.476 --> 00:41:44.778
It's only 10 hours!
I need more time.

00:41:44.812 --> 00:41:45.929
You don't have any more time.

00:41:45.963 --> 00:41:46.947
[Skype closes]

00:41:46.981 --> 00:41:49.366
[♪]

00:41:49.400 --> 00:41:51.534
[Explosion roars]

